        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_2095_2_1</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I'm due to start supervising an Undergrad student who wishes to look at the possibility of a Crime Free Society.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_2095_2_2</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Their ideas are very much in the early stages however they are interested in a comparative analysis of the American and Norwegian justice systems.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_2095_2_3</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Although not my main subject, I've taught undergraduate Criminology/Criminal Justice for 8 years, including many Dissertations - but the concept of a Crime Free Society isn't something I've come across in literature and feels very utopian.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_2095_2_4</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>I'm considering just steering the student towards more of a focus on radical criminal justice approaches but before I do I thought I'd ask in a few different communities/groups I'm part of.</TEXT>
        </DOC>
        <DOC>
            	<DOCNO>s_2095_2_5</DOCNO>
            	<TEXT>Would anybody in this community have any literature they could suggest that would fit the bill?</TEXT>
